rawContent: The early internet tumblr era was crucial for millennials in forming communities and romantic connections but it quickly also became its own form of self-mythologizing giving rise to the “tumblr art hoe” and the infinite genz variations. For people like me at the time, the culture bridged the gap in rural Midwest to the city, academy, and cultural sphere and felt subversive without much social capital attached to our anonymized silos. However, when encountering culture in IRL cities, it was disposable, there were no ends besides as a badge of identity. Hence, why @DeanKissick is correct in saying that profiting from cultural scenes is less about producing genuine art and more about an identity obsession and it’s attempt in making art of self-mythologizing. https://t.co/6cjpmrjxCP
